ENTRY       EC 2.5.1.52                 Enzyme
NAME        L-mimosine synthase;
            O3-acetyl-L-serine acetate-lyase (adding 3,4-dihydroxypyridin-1-yl);
            3-O-acetyl-L-serine:3,4-dihydroxypyridine 1-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)transferase;
            O3-acetyl-L-serine:3,4-dihydroxypyridine 1-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)transferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     O-acetyl-L-serine:3,4-dihydroxypyridine 1-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)transferase
REACTION    O-acetyl-L-serine + 3,4-dihydroxypyridine = 3-(3,4-dihydroxypyridin-1-yl)-L-alanine + acetate [RN:R04091]
ALL_REAC    R04091
SUBSTRATE   O-acetyl-L-serine [CPD:C00979];
            3,4-dihydroxypyridine [CPD:C02932]
PRODUCT     3-(3,4-dihydroxypyridin-1-yl)-L-alanine [CPD:C04446];
            acetate [CPD:C00033]
COMMENT     Brings about the biosynthesis of L-mimosine in plants of the Mimosa and Leucaena genera. Not identical with EC 2.5.1.51, beta-pyrazolylalanine synthase.
HISTORY     EC 2.5.1.52 created 1989 as EC 4.2.99.15, transferred 2002 to EC 2.5.1.52
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Murakoshi, I., Ikegami, F., Hinuma, Y. and Hanma, Y.
  TITLE     Purification and characterization of L-mimosine synthase from Leucaena leucocephala.
  JOURNAL   Phytochemistry 23 (1984) 1905-1908.
